cz.melkamar.andruian.viewlink.data.persistence

Class ParserDatadefPersistor

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.melkamar.andruian.viewlink.data.persistence.ParserDatadefPersistor

  • public class ParserDatadefPersistor
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is responsible for converting and persisting DataDef instances produced by the ddfparser library into local DataDef instances. Also, due to the way Room works, hierarchies of objects need to be saved separately, so this class handles saving all objects that form the DataDef hierarchy.

      • saveParserDatadef

        public static DataDef saveParserDatadef(cz.melkamar.andruian.ddfparser.model.DataDef parserDataDef,
                                        AppDatabase appDatabase)
                                 throws PersistenceException
        Persist a DataDef obtained from the parser as a local bunch of objects.

        The parser class model creates a tree structure, with a DataDef as root. Due to the way Android Room (used for persistence) works, this tree structure needs to be split to several objects that reference each other via foreign keys.

        parserDataDef -

        Construct a DataDef object from the given DataDef returned by a parser.

        Only construct classes that are connected to the DataDef. Do not process anything else - that has to be done separately by calling the appropriate method.
